currentPositions.description:
- Empower and supervise a team of Biochemistry Research Associates who perform biochemical assays within Genmab’s product development activities, focusing on antibody characterization;
- Represent analytical and biochemistry expertise within the CMC department;
- Using different biochemical approaches, to contribute to antibody characterization, stability testing, forced degradation, formulation and QC analysis. Review data generated according to SOPs;
- Work in international project teams, interacting with project, subject matter experts and CMOs/CROs to provide the required quality of data, assays and reports;
- Propose new biochemical and biophysical technologies and are responsible for their implementation;
- Work with external and internal parties to implement automated solutions to improve productivity or expand our capabilities;
- Prepare protocols and document scientific results in reports for the purpose of product development, publications, patents and regulatory documents;
- Proactively look for ways to increase efficiency and optimize work processes.
